3
00:00:08.155 --> 00:00:10.235
The portfolio management office is similar in a way

4
00:00:10.235 --> 00:00:14.185
to the project management office, except it is on steroids.

5
00:00:14.185 --> 00:00:18.185
That is it is tackling very large and complex company initiatives

6
00:00:18.185 --> 00:00:21.195
and we will look at six key activities of the PMO.

7
00:00:21.195 --> 00:00:23.215
The first, initiative demand management.

8
00:00:23.215 --> 00:00:27.175
The PMO will manage initiative planning and prioritization

9
00:00:27.175 --> 00:00:29.205
and the projects and programs within each.

10
00:00:29.205 --> 00:00:33.165
Governance, establishment of initiative management policies.

11
00:00:33.165 --> 00:00:36.700
Then execute the initiatives via projects programs and operations,

12
00:00:36.700 --> 00:00:39.165
on time and on budget.

13
00:00:39.165 --> 00:00:41.825
Define and maintain standards metrics and process for the

14
00:00:41.825 --> 00:00:44.225
running of the PMO office and its activities.

15
00:00:44.225 --> 00:00:47.205
Perform cross-functional reporting and communication.

16
00:00:47.205 --> 00:00:50.245
Now effective communication is even more important.

17
00:00:50.245 --> 00:00:55.185
You need to communicate from the CxO offices and throughout the entire company.

18
00:00:55.185 --> 00:00:58.165
Maximize the company's investment dollar.

19
00:00:58.165 --> 00:01:00.235
Basically that's one of the main goals of the PMO.

20
00:01:00.235 --> 00:01:04.175
To get the greatest bang, business value for the buck.

21
00:01:04.175 --> 00:01:05.225
For your investment dollar.

22
00:01:05.225 --> 00:01:11.155
Now we'll cover each responsibility in detail in the next few slides.

